<% set_meta_tags title: "Policies",
                 description: "Our archive of legal documents, policies, and agreements that govern XIVAuth." %>

<% content_for(:page_header) do %>
  <div>
    <h1>Policy Directory</h1>
    <p>Policies and agreements governing XIVAuth.</p>
  </div>
<% end %>

<p>
  The documents linked below govern the use of XIVAuth and related services, as well as the rights and obligations of
  users and developers. By using XIVAuth, you agree to these policies. Policies may be added, removed, or amended at
  any time.
</p>

<p>
  Please also be aware that we are not lawyers. We've tried to write these documents in a way that is easy to
  understand and makes our intent clear. Please provide us the courtesy of following the general intent of these
  documents, as they're meant to protect you as much as they are meant to protect us.
</p>

<div class="card">
  <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
    <li class="list-group-item position-relative py-3">
      <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3">
        <i class="bi bi-file-text fs-4 text-muted flex-shrink-0"></i>
        <div>
          <%= link_to "Terms of Service", legal_terms_path, class: "fw-semibold stretched-link text-decoration-none" %>
          <p class="mb-0 small text-muted">
            The Terms of Service dictate how you can use the service, your rights and responsibilities, and the legal
            limitations of the platform.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="list-group-item position-relative py-3">
      <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3">
        <i class="bi bi-shield fs-4 text-muted flex-shrink-0"></i>
        <div>
          <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", legal_privacy_path, class: "fw-semibold stretched-link text-decoration-none" %>
          <p class="mb-0 small text-muted">
            The Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information. It also serves as a
            record of our data processors and the commitments we make to protect your privacy. It also outlines how,
            why, and when we share your data with other parties.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="list-group-item position-relative py-3">
      <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3">
        <i class="bi bi-code-square fs-4 text-muted flex-shrink-0"></i>
        <div>
          <%= link_to "Developer Agreement", legal_devagreement_path, class: "fw-semibold stretched-link text-decoration-none" %>
          <p class="mb-0 small text-muted">
            The Developer Agreement outlines the rules and requirements to use XIVAuth in your own project. It includes
            guidelines for how to interact with our data and what we expect from developers in turn.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="list-group-item position-relative py-3">
      <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3">
        <i class="bi bi-bug fs-4 text-muted flex-shrink-0"></i>
        <div>
          <%= link_to "Security Policy", legal_security_path, class: "fw-semibold stretched-link text-decoration-none" %>
          <p class="mb-0 small text-muted">
            The Security Policy explains our commitment to security and includes guidelines for prospective penetration
            testers. It describes how to report security issues to us and what to expect after a report is made.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="list-group-item position-relative py-3">
      <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3">
        <i class="bi bi-person-exclamation fs-4 text-muted flex-shrink-0"></i>
        <div>
          <%= link_to "Moderation Policy", legal_moderation_path, class: "fw-semibold stretched-link text-decoration-none" %>
          <p class="mb-0 small text-muted">
            The Moderation Policy explains how content moderation will be handled, including how we handle user reports,
            remove content, and the actions we may take to uphold the platform's integrity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>